verses.verse: To the <S%H5329>chief<s%> <S%H5329>Musician,<s%> A <S%H4210>Psalm<s%> and <S%H7892>Song<s%> of <S%H1732>David.<s%> <S%H8416>Praise<s%> <S%H1747>waits<s%> for you, O <S%H430>God,<s%> in <S%H6726>Sion:<s%> and to you shall the <S%H5088>vow<s%> be <S%H7999>performed.<s%>
O you that <S%H8085>hear<s%> <S%H8605>prayer,<s%> to you shall <S%H3605>all<s%> <S%H1320>flesh<s%> <S%H935>come.<s%>
<S%H1697>Iniquities<s%> <S%H5771><s%> <S%H1396>prevail<s%> against me: as for our <S%H6588>transgressions,<s%> you shall <S%H3722>purge<s%> them away.

<S%H835>Blessed<s%> is the man whom you <S%H977>choose,<s%> and cause to <S%H7126>approach<s%> to you, that he may <S%H7931>dwell<s%> in your <S%H2691>courts:<s%> we shall be <S%H7646>satisfied<s%> with the <S%H2898>goodness<s%> of your <S%H1004>house,<s%> even of your <S%H6918>holy<s%> <S%H1964>temple.<s%>

By <S%H3372>terrible<s%> things in <S%H6664>righteousness<s%> will you <S%H6030>answer<s%> us, O <S%H430>God<s%> of our <S%H3468>salvation;<s%> who are the <S%H4009>confidence<s%> of <S%H3605>all<s%> the <S%H7099>ends<s%> of the <S%H776>earth,<s%> and of them that are <S%H7350>afar<s%> off on the <S%H3220>sea:<s%>
Which by his <S%H3581>strength<s%> <S%H3559>sets<s%> fast the <S%H2022>mountains;<s%> being <S%H247>girded<s%> with <S%H1369>power:<s%>
Which <S%H7623>stills<s%> the <S%H7588>noise<s%> of the <S%H3220>seas,<s%> the <S%H7588>noise<s%> of their <S%H1530>waves,<s%> and the <S%H1995>tumult<s%> of the <S%H3816>people.<s%>

They also that <S%H3427>dwell<s%> in the <S%H7098>uttermost<s%> parts are <S%H3372>afraid<s%> at your <S%H226>tokens:<s%> you make the <S%H4161>outgoings<s%> of the <S%H1242>morning<s%> and <S%H6153>evening<s%> to <S%H7442>rejoice.<s%>

You <S%H6485>visit<s%> the <S%H776>earth,<s%> and <S%H7783>water<s%> it: you <S%H7227>greatly<s%> <S%H6238>enrich<s%> it with the <S%H6388>river<s%> of <S%H430>God,<s%> which is <S%H4390>full<s%> of <S%H4325>water:<s%> you <S%H3559>prepare<s%> them <S%H1715>corn,<s%> when you have <S%H3651>so<s%> <S%H3559>provided<s%> for it.

You <S%H7301>water<s%> the <S%H8525>ridges<s%> thereof <S%H7301>abundantly:<s%> you <S%H5181>settle<s%> the <S%H1417>furrows<s%> thereof: you make it <S%H4127>soft<s%> with <S%H7241>showers:<s%> you <S%H1288>bless<s%> the <S%H6780>springing<s%> thereof.
You <S%H5849>crown<s%> the <S%H8141>year<s%> with your <S%H2896>goodness;<s%> and your <S%H4570>paths<s%> <S%H7491>drop<s%> <S%H1880>fatness.<s%>
They <S%H7491>drop<s%> on the <S%H4999>pastures<s%> of the <S%H4057>wilderness:<s%> and the little <S%H1389>hills<s%> <S%H1524>rejoice<s%> on every <S%H2296>side.<s%>

The <S%H3733>pastures<s%> are <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H6629>flocks;<s%> the <S%H6010>valleys<s%> also are <S%H5848>covered<s%> <S%H5848>over<s%> with <S%H1250>corn;<s%> they <S%H7321>shout<s%> for joy, they <S%H637>also<s%> <S%H7891>sing.<s%>
